                    "value": "<p><strong>Trigger</strong> A creature attempts to open the door at the end of the hallway</p><hr /><p><strong>Effect</strong> The section of floor marked on the map drops down, becoming a steep ramp. Creatures in the easternmost square fall 5 feet, creatures in the middle square fall 10 feet, and creatures in the western square fall 15 feet (DC 21 to [[/act grab-an-edge dc=21]]). In that order, all creatures who fall are moved to one of the squares immediately east of the marked squares in area <strong>A11</strong>. If any destination square is occupied, the creature in that square is pushed 5 feet to the east as the second creature takes its place, and both creatures take an additional @Damage[2d6[bludgeoning]|traits:nonlethal]{2d6 nonlethal bludgeoning damage} (@Check[reflex|dc:21|basic] save).</p>"
